defs.name: from
defs.docs:
Creates a number from another value that can be converted into
 a primitive via the `ToPrimitive` trait. If the source value cannot be
 represented by the target type, then `None` is returned.

defs.name: AsPrimitive
defs.docs:
A generic interface for casting between machine scalars with the
 `as` operator, which admits narrowing and precision loss.
 Implementers of this trait `AsPrimitive` should behave like a primitive
 numeric type (e.g. a newtype around another primitive), and the
 intended conversion must never fail.

defs.name: rotate_left
defs.docs:
Shifts the bits to the left by a specified amount amount, `n`, wrapping
 the truncated bits to the end of the resulting integer.

defs.name: rotate_right
defs.docs:
Shifts the bits to the right by a specified amount amount, `n`, wrapping
 the truncated bits to the beginning of the resulting integer.

defs.docs:
Shifts the bits to the left by a specified amount amount, `n`, filling
 zeros in the least significant bits.

Shifts the bits to the right by a specified amount amount, `n`, copying
 the "sign bit" in the most significant bits even for unsigned types.

defs.name: unsigned_shl
defs.docs:
Shifts the bits to the left by a specified amount amount, `n`, filling
 zeros in the least significant bits.

defs.name: unsigned_shr
defs.docs:
Shifts the bits to the right by a specified amount amount, `n`, filling
 zeros in the most significant bits.

defs.name: CheckedAdd
defs.docs:
Performs addition that returns `None` instead of wrapping around on
 overflow.

defs.name: checked_add
defs.docs:
Adds two numbers, checking for overflow. If overflow happens, `None` is
 returned.

defs.name: CheckedSub
defs.docs: Performs subtraction that returns `None` instead of wrapping around on underflow.

defs.name: checked_sub
defs.docs:
Subtracts two numbers, checking for underflow. If underflow happens,
 `None` is returned.

defs.name: CheckedMul
defs.docs:
Performs multiplication that returns `None` instead of wrapping around on underflow or
 overflow.

defs.name: checked_mul
defs.docs:
Multiplies two numbers, checking for underflow or overflow. If underflow
 or overflow happens, `None` is returned.

defs.name: CheckedDiv
defs.docs:
Performs division that returns `None` instead of panicking on division by zero and instead of
 wrapping around on underflow and overflow.

defs.name: checked_div
defs.docs:
Divides two numbers, checking for underflow, overflow and division by
 zero. If any of that happens, `None` is returned.

defs.name: CheckedRem
defs.docs:
Performs an integral remainder that returns `None` instead of panicking on division by zero and
 instead of wrapping around on underflow and overflow.

defs.name: checked_rem
defs.docs:
Finds the remainder of dividing two numbers, checking for underflow, overflow and division
 by zero. If any of that happens, `None` is returned.

defs.name: CheckedNeg
defs.docs: Performs negation that returns `None` if the result can't be represented.

defs.name: checked_neg
defs.docs:
Negates a number, returning `None` for results that can't be represented, like signed `MIN`
 values that can't be positive, or non-zero unsigned values that can't be negative.

defs.name: CheckedShl
defs.docs:
Performs a left shift that returns `None` on shifts larger than
 the type width.

defs.name: checked_shl
defs.docs:
Checked shift left. Computes `self << rhs`, returning `None`
 if `rhs` is larger than or equal to the number of bits in `self`.

defs.name: CheckedShr
defs.docs:
Performs a right shift that returns `None` on shifts larger than
 the type width.

defs.name: checked_shr
defs.docs:
Checked shift right. Computes `self >> rhs`, returning `None`
 if `rhs` is larger than or equal to the number of bits in `self`.

Fused multiply-add. Computes `(self * a) + b` with only one rounding
 error, yielding a more accurate result than an unfused multiply-add.

defs.docs: The resulting type after applying the fused multiply-add.

defs.name: wrapping_sub

Wrapping (modular) subtraction. Computes `self - other`, wrapping around at the boundary

defs.name: WrappingMul
defs.docs: Performs multiplication that wraps around on overflow.

defs.name: wrapping_mul
defs.docs:
Wrapping (modular) multiplication. Computes `self * other`, wrapping around at the boundary
 of the type.

defs.name: WrappingShl
defs.docs: Performs a left shift that does not panic.

defs.name: wrapping_shl
defs.docs:
Panic-free bitwise shift-left; yields `self << mask(rhs)`,
 where `mask` removes any high order bits of `rhs` that would
 cause the shift to exceed the bitwidth of the type.

defs.name: WrappingShr
defs.docs: Performs a right shift that does not panic.

defs.name: wrapping_shr
defs.docs:
Panic-free bitwise shift-right; yields `self >> mask(rhs)`,
 where `mask` removes any high order bits of `rhs` that would
 cause the shift to exceed the bitwidth of the type.
